Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from contrast enhanced box in Page 03
And	I'm on Page 04 of Feet MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Arthritis' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And a multiple selection localizer is enabled

And 'Moderate' radio button is enabled
And 'Marked' radio button is enabled

And 'Articular effusion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Synovitis' checkbox is enabled

And 'Erosions' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intraosseous cysts' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chondropathy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Periostitis' checkbox is enabled

And 'Proliferative bone changes' checkbox is enabled
And 'Destructions' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ankylosis' checkbox is enabled

And 'Rheumatoid Arthritis' radio button is enabled
And 'Psoriatic Arthritis' radio button is enabled
And 'Tophaceus gout' radio button is enabled

When I click on 'Talocrural joint' part on the canvas
And I click on 'Subtalar joint' part on the canvas
Then 'Talocrural joint' part is selected
And 'Subtalar joint' part is selected

When I select 'Synovitis' checkbox
Then 'Hyperplasia' checkbox is enabled
And 'T2w hyperintense' checkbox is enabled
And 'Increased contrast enhancement' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pannus' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Erosions' checkbox
Then 'Joint facet' radio button is enabled
And 'At the capsular insertion' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Bone marrow edema' checkbox
Then 'Subchondral' radio button is enabled
And 'Diaphyseal' radio button is enabled
